name: Subtractions
description:
You've got two numbers. As long as they are both larger than zero, they go
through the same operation: subtract the lesser number from the larger one. If
they equal substract one number from the another. For example, one operation
transforms pair (4,17) to pair (4,13), it transforms (5,5) to (0,5). You've
got some number of pairs (ai, bi). How many operations will be performed for
each of them? Input The first line contains the number of pairs n (1 ≤ n ≤
1000). Then follow n lines, each line contains a pair of positive integers ai,
bi (1 ≤ ai, bi ≤ 10^9). Output Print the sought number of operations for each
pair on a single line. Examples Input 2 4 17 7 987654321 Output 8 141093479
